{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17591872","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17591872"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T10:07:29+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T10:07:29+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15216"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15216","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15216"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.06,0.13,0.03,0,0.77]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7907"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65308"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7907","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7907"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15216"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50746"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1051"},{"type":"tags","id":"3549"},{"type":"tags","id":"3817"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"},{"type":"tags","id":"9267"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19267"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19270"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21684"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65308","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/65308"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ESome 2500 new cases of gastric cancer are diagnosed every year in Australia. The disease occurs twice as frequently in men compared with women. The overall 5-year survival rate is 36%. Many patients will present with advanced disease; perhaps the main reason for this is the lack of specificity of early symptoms.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following symptoms suggests advanced rather than early disease?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Bloating","Dyspepsia","Heartburn","Nausea","Weight loss"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBloating, dyspepsia\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003Eheartburn \u003C/strong\u003Eand \u003Cstrong\u003Enausea\u003C/strong\u003E are non-specific symptoms that can occur in both early and advanced gastric cancer. They are also symptoms that are more often associated with benign processes, such as gastro-oesophageal reflux disease, peptic ulcer disease, gallstones and irritable bowel syndrome.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe addition of (unintentional) weight loss to any of the above symptoms should alert the clinician that the patient\u0027s symptoms need to be further explored and various investigations considered.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere are a number of signs that might point towards an advanced gastric cancer and these include:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETroisier sign or Virchow node (enlarged left supraclavicular lymph node) (Image 1)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESister Mary Joseph nodule (periumbilical metastasis) (Image 2)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EKrukenberg tumours (ovarian metastases)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIrish node (left axillary node)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Advanced gastric adenocarcinoma commonly presents with weight loss, early satiety, and epigastric pain","Troisier sign (left supraclavicular lymphadenopathy) is a specific sign of metastatic disease, often gastric cancer","Sister Mary Joseph nodule indicates periumbilical metastasis from intra-abdominal malignancy"],"references":["Arnold M, Abnet CC, Neale RE, Vignat J, Giovannucci EL, McGlynn KA, Bray F. Global Burden of 5 Major Types of Gastrointestinal Cancer. Gastroenterology. 2020 Jul;159(1):335-349.e15. doi: 10.1053/j.gastro.2020.02.068. Epub 2020 Apr 2. PMID: 32247694; PMCID: PMC8630546","Goh PMY, Lenzi JE. Benign tumors of the duodenum and stomach. In: Holzheimer RG, Mannick JA, editors. Surgical Treatment: Evidence-Based and Problem-Oriented. Munich: Zuckschwerdt; 2001. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK6948/","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Sexton RE, Al Hallak MN, Diab M, Azmi AS. Gastric cancer: a comprehensive review of current and future treatment strategies. Cancer Metastasis Rev. 2020 Dec;39(4):1179-1203. doi: 10.1007/s10555-020-09925-3. Epub 2020 Sep 7. PMID: 32894370; PMCID: PMC7680370"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50746"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15216"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21236"},{"type":"media","id":"21237"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21236","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21236"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/QzIdDRg0XC5XQZfxr0pP0uxN8H1VGg.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/QzIdDRg0XC5XQZfxr0pP0uxN8H1VGg.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":547,"height":600}},{"type":"media","id":"21237","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21237"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/ty35PGqdssXjfuzBuc1KghrycvIApk.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/ty35PGqdssXjfuzBuc1KghrycvI